{{Documentation subpage}}

The converter [[Template:Convert/3]] will convert 3 amounts at once, allowing a mix of different range words between the 3 amounts. However, all 3 amounts are treated as the same unit type. The output unit must be specified, or put "0" for the default output unit.

===Usage===
: <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5|by|6|by|7|m|ft}}</nowiki>
: <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5|x|6|x|7|m|ft}}</nowiki>
: <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5|-|6|-|7|m|ft}}</nowiki>
: <nowiki>{{convert/3 |7|to|8|by|4.5|km|mi|abbr=on}}</nowiki>
The template has the same parameters as [[Template:Convert]], and so it allows abbreviation abbr=in or abbr=out or abbr=none, wikilinks lk=in or lk=out, and adjective mode adj=on. The separator can also be a semicolon: disp=semi, disp=semicolon, disp=or, disp=comma & disp=b (default parentheses). Using optional parameter "warn=yes" will warn when the separator is an unusual word (other than: to, by, and, or, -, +/-, x, xx or comma).

===Examples===
The following examples show a mixture of "by" & "x" or "to" in some conversions:
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5|by|6|by|7|m|ft}}</nowiki>{{spaces|5}}gives: {{convert/3 |5|by|6|by|7|m|ft}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5|x|6|x|7|m|ft}}</nowiki>{{spaces|8}}gives: {{convert/3 |5|x|6|x|7|m|ft}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |7|to|8|to|9|km|mi}}</nowiki>{{spaces|16}}gives: {{convert/3 |7|to|8|to|9|km|mi}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |7|to|8|to|9|km|mi|abbr=on}}</nowiki>{{spaces|4}}gives: {{convert/3 |7|to|8|to|9|km|mi|abbr=on}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |7|to|8|to|9|km|mi|adj=on}}</nowiki>{{spaces|6}}gives: {{convert/3 |7|to|8|to|9|km|mi|adj=on}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5|to|6|by|7|m|ft}}</nowiki>{{spaces|5}}gives: {{convert/3 |5|to|6|by|7|m|ft}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5|by|6|x|7|m|ft}}</nowiki>{{spaces|6}}gives: {{convert/3 |5|by|6|x|7|m|ft}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |10|-|20|-|30|°C|F|disp=or}}</nowiki>{{spaces|9}}gives: {{convert/3 |10|-|20|-|30|°C|F|disp=or}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |11|-|22|-|33|°C|F|disp=semi}}</nowiki>{{spaces|5}}gives: {{convert/3 |11|-|22|-|33|°C|F|disp=semi}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |40|-|50|-|60|°F|C|lk=on }}</nowiki>{{spaces|5}}gives: {{convert/3 |40|-|50|-|60|°F|C|lk=on}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |45|-|55|-|65|°F|C|lk=out}}</nowiki>{{spaces|5}}gives: {{convert/3 |45|-|55|-|65|°F|C|lk=out}}
* <nowiki>{{convert/3 |5+1/2|by|6+1/3|x|7+1/4|m|ft}}</nowiki>{{spaces|4}}gives: {{convert/3 |5+1/2|by|6+1/3|x|7+1/4|m|ft}}

The range-words are: to, by, and, or, -, +/-, x, xx & comma. Display types: disp=comma, disp=semi, disp=or, disp=s, disp=2 (or disp=out), disp=# (or disp=number) and disp=b. The results are identical to using Template:Convert for each amount individually.
