'''[[Template:Convert/Dual/LoffAoffDxSoff]]''' converts a range of numbers, while displaying custom separators around the output amounts. Examples:
:* <nowiki>{{convert|3|-|6|cm|ft|disp=x| long (or |)}}</nowiki> &rarr; {{convert|3|-|6|cm|ft|disp=x| long (or |)}}
:* <nowiki>{{convert|4|-|7|km|mi|disp=x|, same as }}</nowiki> &rarr; {{convert|3|-|6|cm|ft|disp=x|, same as }}

This subtemplate is invoked from whichever range-word subtemplate is used, such as {{tl|Convert/-}} or {{tl|Convert/to}} (etc.) using the name "Dual/LoffAoffDxSoff" and passing parameters {6} & {7} as being parameters {5} & {6} here.
